  "texts": [
    "This is particularly useful in dynamic environments where the information changes frequently or is too specialized to be captured fully by a pre-trained model.",
    "For example, in our multi-source question-answer system, RAG can enable the retrieval of information from both contract documents and databases, ensuring the responses are relevant to the specific user's question.",
    "The chunking strategy used in RAG is critical to its success, as it determines how documents are divided into smaller pieces for embedding and retrieval.",
    "By effectively segmenting large documents, RAG ensures that only the most relevant sections are retrieved and fed into the LLM, preventing information overload and improving the precision of the answer.",
    "The choice of similarity metrics, such as Cosine or Euclidean distance, plays a significant role in determining which chunks are selected for retrieval [Gao et al., 2023b]."
  ],
